// =============================================================================
// core/database/sqlite/native/auth/mod.vr
// =============================================================================
// Layer: 6
// Spec: sqlite-native.md §19.5 (authorizer hook integration)
//
// Authorization is the connection-level pre-compile gate that says
// "yes / no / ignore" for every privileged action the SQL compiler
// is about to compile (read column, write table, drop view, …).
// It's the loom equivalent of `sqlite3_set_authorizer`.
//
// The dispatch is two-level:
//   1. `Authorizer` aggregates one or more `AuthorizerHook`
//      implementations. Multiple hooks compose by intersection —
//      the most restrictive decision wins.
//   2. The L5 codegen calls `authorize(action)` before emitting any
//      opcode for that action; the result determines whether to
//      compile, refuse, or substitute a NULL.
//
// The hook list is stored deterministically (insertion order) so DST
// runs reproduce identical decisions.
// =============================================================================

module core.database.sqlite.native.auth;

public module decision;
public module dispatch;
public module action;
